# How to set up FFmpeg on Windows (for dummies)
To get started with [[Notes/FFmpeg\|FFmpeg]], follow these steps:
1. Download [[Notes/FFmpeg\|FFmpeg]].
	1. Go to [official download page](https://www.ffmpeg.org/download.html).
	2. Scroll down and click on the following: ![Pasted image 20220120173948.png](data:image/png;base64,)
	3. On the page that opened, scroll down and click on the following: ![Pasted image 20220120174044.png](data:image/png;base64,)
2. Prepare to use.
	1. Extract the downloaded file (extract to anywhere you want).
	2. Open the extracted folder, and then open the `bin` folder: ![Pasted image 20220120174255.png](data:image/png;base64,) The `bin` folder should contain these 3 files: ![Pasted image 20220120174422.png](data:image/png;base64,)
	3. When inside the `bin` folder, type `cmd` in the folder path and press enter. This should open a terminal window within this folder.![Pasted image 20220120174824.png](data:image/png;base64,)
3. Now you can start using [[Notes/FFmpeg\|FFmpeg]] in the opened terminal by typing `ffmpeg`.
